pr_body:
@wlach I could use your assistance here. I'm having a perf alert + a list containing 5 pushes. The 3rd push is associated with the alert, while the other 4 are just neighboring pushes (2 before, 2 after the 3rd push).
This background worker I'm working on must go through all these 5 pushes and check to see if there are any pending jobs that must run/are running perf tests with the same signature as those that created the perf alert.
In short: how can I find the jobs that produced data points for a particular perf alert?

…ing on older system (centos 6).

This should fix an issue where older systems fail to build NuPIC due to glibc incompatability.

